<TITLE> Banks, courts reopen after Eid </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 23 (bdnews24.com)Government offices, banks and courts reopened Sunday after a three-day Eid break. The Eid hangover, however, was far from over. Attendance in the offices was thin. Many are enjoying prolonged holidays in addition to the Eid vacation. Most offices at the Bangladesh Secretariat were empty as a small number of officials and supporting staff returned to work. Most were busy exchanging Eid greetings. Emdad Haque, security guard at the Secretariat main entrance, told bdnews24.com: "A few government vehicles entered the complex. The number of visitors was quite limited." The banks that reopened Sunday are likely to see brisk activities after the three-day closure, bankers said. Some private businesses in the financial district of Motijheel reopened. District sessions judge's courts and metropolitan magistrate's courts reopened with lawyers arriving to join the proceedings of their cases. Many magistrates were present in their chambers after the Eid break, the bdnews24.com legal affairs correspondent reports from the Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court. bdnews24.
